==English==

===Noun===
'''virii''' (''plural:'' '''N/A''')

# sometimes used as a plural form of [[virus]]
# {{cattag|Computing}}: A superset of computer software composed of computer [[virus|viruses]], [[trojan|trojans]], and [[worms]].

====Usage notes====
*The plural '''virii''', though common, is generally considered to be incorrect, and based on a misunderstanding of Latin. There is no plural for the Latin word ''virus''; using the native English pluralisation rules, to yield ''viruses'', would arguably then be most correct.
*The term '''virii''' in the computing sense is often used by individuals who collect, trade, and produce these kinds of software.


